<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rebel2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rebel,</orth> vb. to rise in violent opposition against lawful authority, to revolt: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 37</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.119" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.391" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 391</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 96</bibl>. With <cit><quote>against:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.379" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 379</bibl></cit>. Cor, <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 1, 100</bibl>. With <emph>to,</emph> in the same sense: <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 33</bibl>.
